<subSubSection id="123162473963F82C2D5C9BCB406D9307" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="60DCB583B3BFA1DFC0EE70BF1B1C9299" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
<pageBreakToken id="BA974C6F6257828A371E589F7B2BCE29" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" start="start">Etymology</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8361EE76D8D221297AD0A4FF11159909" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
The species is named in honor of Dr. Max M.J. van Balgooy, a specialist of the SE Asian flora. Dr. van Balgooy has annotated the herbarium sheets of this new species stating that it is an &quot;unusual 
<taxonomicName id="759779E3276A6E3D3A6C8AD691AB01F0" genus="Rutaceae" lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" rank="genus">Rutaceae</taxonomicName>
near 
<taxonomicName id="C263BD0CC0095BAA6CFB67989153EAFE" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Platydesma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="427A1FF4EA2F4965099A940CAA2DD936" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Platydesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;. Phylogenetic studies (
<bibRefCitation id="1D54CCBB0E79944AD1A25A9C28727ECD" author="Harbaugh, DT" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Biogeography" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" pagination="230 - 241" publicationUrl="10.1111/j.1365-2699.2008.02008.x" refId="B5" refString="Harbaugh, DT, Wagner, WL, Allan, GJ, Zimmer, EA, 2009. The Hawaiian Archipelago is a stepping stone for dispersal in the Pacific: an example from the plant genus Melicope (Rutaceae). Journal of Biogeography 36 (2): 230 - 241, DOI: 10.1111/j.1365-2699.2008.02008.x" title="The Hawaiian Archipelago is a stepping stone for dispersal in the Pacific: an example from the plant genus Melicope (Rutaceae)." url="10.1111/j.1365-2699.2008.02008.x" volume="36" year="2009">Harbaugh et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F8C6E8B4D556B71F1A736024221C2339" author="Appelhans, MS" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" pagination="54 - 68" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.ympev.2014.06.014" refId="B1" refString="Appelhans, MS, Wen, J, Wagner, WL, 2014a. A molecular phylogeny of Acronychia, Euodia, Melicope and relatives (Rutaceae) reveals polyphyletic genera and key innovations for species richness. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 79: 54 - 68, DOI: 10.1016/j.ympev.2014.06.014" title="A molecular phylogeny of Acronychia, Euodia, Melicope and relatives (Rutaceae) reveals polyphyletic genera and key innovations for species richness." url="10.1016/j.ympev.2014.06.014" volume="79" year="2014 a">Appelhans et al. 2014a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A3FFD8F6BC147500DDA438792DD529BF" author="Appelhans, MS" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" pagination="425 - 448" publicationUrl="10.1111/boj.12123" refId="B2" refString="Appelhans, MS, Wen, J, Wood, KR, Allan, GJ, Zimmer, EA, Wagner, WL, 2014b. Molecular phylogenetic analysis of Hawaiian Rutaceae (Melicope, Platydesma and Zanthoxylum) and their different colonisation patterns. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 174: 425 - 448, DOI: 10.1111/boj.12123" title="Molecular phylogenetic analysis of Hawaiian Rutaceae (Melicope, Platydesma and Zanthoxylum) and their different colonisation patterns." url="10.1111/boj.12123" volume="174" year="2014 b">2014b</bibRefCitation>
) have shown that 
<taxonomicName id="DEFE2A9AE37DA44983DD7A357DABA045" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Platydesma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7053FAAC704977B3A5063429BACAFBE9" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Platydesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is included within 
<taxonomicName id="FE5A54F296BE0D01C6ED6D49699D527A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="129B6F1BF47C97FF1D53840F87FE5AE9" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Melicope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, proving Dr. van 
<normalizedToken id="C21BB77C880604EA15330FB366A60EF3" originalValue="Balgooy’s">Balgooy's</normalizedToken>
assumptions to be true. In addition to 
<taxonomicName id="393F8462BF0B15F0EB75E3AC8AEF3C8F" authorityName="T. G. Hartley" authorityYear="2001" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maxii">
<emphasis id="2165518B988E65A3CA7EC830873587EF" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Melicope maxii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
T.G. Hartley, which is endemic to Sulawesi (Indonesia), 
<taxonomicName id="07191F5CB18445EFFB800BE1A933F48B" authorityName="Appelhans, W. L. Wagner &amp; K. R. Wood" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balgooyi">
<emphasis id="39E6E0A50D3304A33B9AD21296A316E2" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Melicope balgooyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the second species of 
<taxonomicName id="1B34D18EB4177F6630ACA277EF60F0A7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DE04D99C43ECC39ABB503C827AF95C4C" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Melicope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
named after Dr. van Balgooy.
</paragraph>
